Nick Clegg said wealthy people with holiday homes would not mind having to 'chip in a bit' to protect services in areas where one in 10 homes are vacant . 
  Well-off buying up homes in tourist hotspots has driven up property values . 
  Lib Dem plan launched in Cornwall today would see 200 per cent council tax charged . 
  Levy would be used to deter people from buying holiday homes in the first place . 
 